
[1]slipperiness

   SLIP'PERINESS, n.

   1. The state or quality of being slippery; lubricity; smoothness;
   glibness; as the slipperiness of ice or snow; the slipperiness of the
   tongue.

   2. Uncertainty; want of firm footing.

   3. Lubricity of character.
